From: AORUS 5090 platform repo <aobersnel@apnex.com.au>
Date: 2026-05-03
Subject: [PATCH] nvdDumpAllEngines_IMPL: per-iteration guard, break on GPU-lost

Lever J-2 patch from /root/aorus-5090-gpu. Targets
NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules at tag 595.71.05.

Background
----------
nvdDumpAllEngines_IMPL iterates through every engine callback (~14 on
Blackwell GB202), invoking each via GSP RPC. The existing loop checks
PDB_PROP_GPU_INACCESSIBLE *after* each callback failure but only sets
a local advisory flag (pNvDumpState->bGpuAccessible = NV_FALSE) -- it
does NOT break out of the loop. Result: 14 successive failed RPCs
when GPU is lost (captured in
/root/ollama/archive/lite-2026-05-03-211751/).

The existing guard also doesn't check PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST, only
PDB_PROP_GPU_INACCESSIBLE. These are different properties.

Fix
---
Insert a per-iteration guard at the top of the loop that checks BOTH
PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST and PDB_PROP_GPU_INACCESSIBLE, sets the advisory
flag, and breaks out of the loop.

Defence-in-depth: companion patch 0002 short-circuits rcdbAddRmGpuDump
at entry, so this loop should never be reached on a known-lost GPU.
But if some other entry path (test harness, control IOCTL) calls
nvdDumpAllEngines_IMPL directly, this patch ensures the loop still
exits cleanly.

Adds an NV_DBG_ERRORS-level marker so we can observe the patch firing
in dmesg.

Related
-------
- /root/aorus-5090-gpu/docs/source-review-notes.md (Pass 5 + Pass 6 +
  Pass 8)
- patches/0002-rcdbAddRmGpuDump-shortcircuit-on-gpu-lost.patch (the
  primary fix; this patch is defence-in-depth)

---
 src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/nv_debug_dump.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/nv_debug_dump.c b/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/nv_debug_dump.c
--- a/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/nv_debug_dump.c
+++ b/src/nvidia/src/kernel/diagnostics/nv_debug_dump.c
@@ -269,6 +269,18 @@ nvdDumpAllEngines_IMPL
     for (pEngineCallback = pNvd->pCallbacks;
         (prbEncBufLeft(pPrbEnc) > 0) && (pEngineCallback != NULL);
         pEngineCallback = pEngineCallback->pNext)
     {
+        //
+        // AORUS Lever J-2 patch (2026-05-03):
+        // Per-iteration guard. The existing PDB_PROP_GPU_INACCESSIBLE
+        // check below sets the advisory flag but does NOT break the
+        // loop. Result on GPU loss: ~14 sequential failed RPCs (one
+        // per engine). Add an explicit break here, and also check the
+        // sibling PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST property which the existing
+        // code does not consult.
+        //
+        if (pGpu->getProperty(pGpu, PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST) ||
+            pGpu->getProperty(pGpu, PDB_PROP_GPU_INACCESSIBLE))
+        {
+            NV_PRINTF(LEVEL_ERROR,
+                      "AORUS Lever J-2 (nvdDumpAllEngines): GPU lost/inaccessible, skipping remaining engine dumps\n");
+            pNvDumpState->bGpuAccessible = NV_FALSE;
+            break;
+        }
+
         NV_CHECK_OK_OR_CAPTURE_FIRST_ERROR(nvStatus, LEVEL_ERROR,
             nvdEngineDumpCallbackHelper(pGpu, pPrbEnc, pNvDumpState, pEngineCallback));

